libsidplayfp 3.0.1  +  libresidfp 1.0.2

Vendored here:
  lib/libsidplayfp.a          static library (arm64), built from source
  lib/libresidfp.a            static library (arm64), built from source
  include/sidplayfp/          public headers (libsidplayfp 3.0.1)
  LICENSE.libsidplayfp        license text (GNU GPL v2 or later)

Why two archives:
  libsidplayfp 3.0.0 dropped the bundled reSID emulation and moved the
  full-quality reSIDfp engine into a separate library, libresidfp. The
  Homebrew bottle is therefore SIDLite-only (no filter-curve control). To
  get the ReSIDfpBuilder (filter6581Curve / filter8580Curve), libsidplayfp
  must be rebuilt from source with libresidfp present; the resulting
  libsidplayfp.a contains both the SIDLite and reSIDfp builders, and the
  reSIDfp DSP symbols live in libresidfp.a (so both archives are linked).

